\b Notes on saving\par
\b0 If going from standard to extended you can compress out all the tracks with 0 sectors if you turn on the option.\par
\par
If going from extended to standard and the track sizes vary you will get a warning about all sizes being set to maximum. You can turn this off in the options.  Converting from extended to standard results in larger file sizes and potentially less accurate files.\par
\par
Saving in standard format writes the header/creator as per the DSK format specification.  Most standard disk images out there are created by DU54 which write the creator/disk-info block wrongly (though we fudgingly read them in okay).\par
\par
It\rquote s called \ldblquote Save copy as\'85\rdblquote  for a reason, don\rquote t overwrite anything important, who knows what may happen.\par
